  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nAnvil\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [ ] Foundry\r\n- [ ] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nnightly-c78a811a8af95fb1e029427583a07b2ca3a3fa51\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nNot clear this is really a bug per se, however see https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/issues/4136 ... should anvil perhaps protect against sending 0 return values for any percentile? I am not sure if any spec (for either eth_feehistory or the EVM in general) either already does or SHOULD specify that 0 fees are nonsense. I suppose it takes a rather special invocation of anvil to cause this (`--base-fee 1`), and protecting 0 return values in certain fields is arguably more about protecting against naive calcs in the calling program (hardhat/cast/foundry scripts/etc)",
